channel.title: Error on compile
channel.description: Hi i changed votting website in client.java and i got this error on compile: client.java:12478: unclosed string literal menuActionName[1] = " ^ client.java:12479: unclosed string literal "; ^ client.java:12480: ']' expected menuActionID[1] = 1005; ^ client.java:12480: illegal start of expression menuActionID[1] = 1005; ^ 4 errors Press any key to continue . . .

item.title: Error on compile
item.dc:creator: @Zosedan Zosedan
item.description:
@Zosedan wrote:

[quote=“Joseph69, post:7, topic:427020”][quote author=RandQm link=topic=529722.msg3866679#msg3866679 date=1325044797]

[quote author=Joseph69 link=topic=529722.msg3866616#msg3866616 date=1325043001]

No, i hate teamviewer and i just finished removing vista security 2012 virus from someone’s computer via teamviewer and im done for today, sorry
Links that will help:
client.java:12480: illegal start of expression
client.java:12478: unclosed string literal

EDIT: client.java:12480: ‘]’ expected for this, you are missing a ‘]’ bracket on what seems to be line 12480 of your client.java, to find out where the ‘lines’ are download notepad++ and look at the numbering on the side
[/quote]omggg:( i need heelpp this error weird and i dont get those messages things…

] acorn explained

unclosed string literal
you have to close your string obviously… with a "
[/quote]dude im on the line of 12480 , cant find any problem[/quote]

Then you’re not looking hard enough. Unicron’s right, the unclosed string literal error appears when you start a string but don’t close it.
